Here is a Frontend Website Testing Plan (Manual + Commands) focused on client-side security testing (very important for bug bounty and web pentesting).

Frontend Testing Plan 🖥️
Phase 1 — Browser Inspection
1. Check Source Code

Open website → press:

Ctrl + U

Look for:

✔ Hidden endpoints
✔ API keys
✔ Comments
✔ Debug info
✔ JS files

Phase 2 — Developer Tools Testing

Open DevTools:

F12

Test these tabs:

Elements Tab

Check:

✔ Hidden inputs
✔ Disabled buttons
✔ Admin fields

Example test:

Change:

<input type="hidden" value="user">

to:

<input value="admin">
Console Testing

Test JavaScript errors:

Example:

alert(document.cookie)

Check:

✔ Cookies
✔ Tokens
✔ Errors

Network Tab Testing

Look for:

✔ API requests
✔ Authorization tokens
✔ POST requests
✔ JSON data

Filter:

Fetch/XHR

Check responses for:

✔ Sensitive data
✔ User IDs
✔ Emails
✔ Tokens

Phase 3 — JavaScript Testing
Extract JS files:

View:

Sources tab

or command:

gau target.com | grep .js
Analyze JS:

Tools:

linkfinder -i https://target.com/app.js

Find:

✔ API endpoints
✔ Secrets
✔ Tokens
✔ Internal URLs

Phase 4 — Input Testing

Test all inputs:

✔ Login
✔ Search
✔ Contact forms
✔ Upload forms

Test payloads:

XSS test:
<script>alert(1)</script>
"><img src=x onerror=alert(1)>
HTML Injection:
<h1>test</h1>
Event Injection:
" onmouseover="alert(1)
Phase 5 — Authentication Testing

Test:

✔ Login bypass
✔ Password reset
✔ Session handling

Try:

Change request in DevTools:

role=user → role=admin

Check response.

Phase 6 — Client Side Storage Testing

Check:

Application tab → Storage

Look:

✔ Local Storage
✔ Session Storage
✔ Cookies

Check for:

✔ JWT tokens
✔ User data
✔ Emails

Console command:

localStorage
sessionStorage
Phase 7 — CORS Testing

Check in Network tab:

Look for:

Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *

Command:

curl -I https://target.com
Phase 8 — UI Logic Testing

Test:

✔ Change prices
✔ Change quantity
✔ Remove restrictions

Example:

Change:

price: 100

to:

price: 1

Check if accepted.

Phase 9 — Frontend Security Headers

Command:

curl -I https://target.com

Check:

✔ CSP
✔ X-Frame
✔ HSTS
✔ XSS Protection

Phase 10 — Frontend Bug Checklist ✔️

Always test:

✔ XSS
✔ DOM XSS
✔ HTML injection
✔ JS secrets
✔ IDOR via frontend API
✔ CORS issues
✔ Clickjacking
✔ Token exposure
✔ Debug endpoints
✔ Source maps (.map files)
